.TH et_viewer 3 "et 1.7.3" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
et_viewer \- Displays a sequence chart for trace events (messages/actions)

.SH DESCRIPTION
.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBactors() :: [term()].\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBfirst_key() :: term().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBoption() ::\fR
\fB          {title, string()} |\fR
\fB          {detail_level, 0..100} |\fR
\fB          {is_suspended, boolean()} |\fR
\fB          {scale, integer()} |\fR
\fB          {width, integer()} |\fR
\fB          {height, integer()} |\fR
\fB          {collector_pid, pid() | undefined} |\fR
\fB          {active_filter, atom()} |\fR
\fB          {max_events, integer() | undefined} |\fR
\fB          {max_actors, integer() | undefined} |\fR
\fB          {actors, actors()} |\fR
\fB          {first_event, first_key()} |\fR
\fB          {hide_unknown, boolean()} |\fR
\fB          {hide_actions, boolean()} |\fR
\fB          {display_mode,\fR
\fB           all |\fR
\fB           {search_actors, forward | reverse, first_key(), actors()}}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBfile(FileName :: file:filename()) -> {ok, pid()} | {error, term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Start a new event viewer and a corresponding collector and load them with trace events from a trace file.


.RE
.B
\fBget_collector_pid(ViewerPid :: pid()) -> pid().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the identifier of the collector process.


.RE
.B
\fBstart() -> {ok, pid()} | {error, term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Simplified start of a sequence chart viewer with global tracing activated.

.PP
Convenient to be used from the command line (erl -s et_viewer).


.RE
.B
\fBstart(GUIorOptions) -> {ok, Viewer :: pid()} | {error, term()}\fR
\fB               when\fR
\fB                   GUIorOptions :: wx | default | Options,\fR
\fB                   Options :: [option() | et_collector:option()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Start of a sequence chart viewer without linking to the parent process.


.RE
.B
\fBstart_link(GUIorOptions) ->\fR
\fB                    {ok, Viewer :: pid()} | {error, term()}\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        GUIorOptions :: wx | default | Options,\fR
\fB                        Options :: [option() | et_collector:option()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Start a sequence chart viewer for trace events (messages/actions)

.PP
A filter_fun() takes an event record as sole argument and returns \fIfalse | true | {true, NewEvent}\fR.

.PP
If the \fIcollector_pid\fR is \fIundefined\fR a new \fIet_collector\fR will be started with the following parameter settings: \fIparent_pid\fR, \fIevent_order\fR, \fItrace_global\fR, \fItrace_pattern\fR, \fItrace_port\fR, \fItrace_max_queue\fR, \fItrace_client\fR, \fIdict_insert\fR and \fIdict_delete\fR. The new \fIet_viewer\fR will register itself as an \fIet_collector\fR subscriber.

.PP
Default values:


.sp
